The DIKSHA is a flagship digital learning platform developed by the Ministry of Education to strengthen technology-enabled education across the country. Designed for students, teachers, and parents, DIKSHA integrates artificial intelligence tools to make learning more accessible, interactive, and inclusive.

One of the platform’s key AI-driven features is smart keyword search in educational videos, which helps learners quickly locate specific concepts within lessons. It also includes a read-aloud function for visually impaired students, enabling them to access digital textbooks and learning materials through audio support. These tools ensure that learning resources are accessible to students with diverse needs.

Available as a mobile application and web platform, DIKSHA offers curriculum-aligned courses, teaching resources, quizzes, and interactive modules based on national and state education boards. Teachers can use it for professional development and classroom support, while students and parents can access structured study material aligned with the school curriculum.

By leveraging AI and digital technologies, DIKSHA is helping transform India’s education system—making quality learning resources widely accessible, inclusive, and personalised for millions of learners across the country.
